	Potter poll    
	 London, March 4 (Reuters): Harry Potter has beaten The Da Vinci Code in a survey of which books Britons most want to pass on to the next generation.      
	One in five people chose the J.K. Rowling series, allowing it to top the list ahead of American author Dan Browns religious thriller, according to a survey for World Book Day.      
	It also revealed that books are still a popular gift as three in four adults gave a book as a present in the past year, with people in Scotland leading the way.    
	Hot Moss    
	 London (PTI): Supermodel Kate Moss proved that common sense always comes after fashion sense for her after stepping out in a pair of leather hotpants despite the below zero temperatures. Moss ventured out into a chilly London in a revealing outfit consisting of hot pants and knee-high boots which she paired with a military jacket, reports the Daily Mail.     
	Bridget TV    
	 London (PTI): After two hit movies, Bridget Jones is set to make a splash on the small screen with a show revolving around the character played by Renee Zellweger in the pipeline. NBC bosses are in the process of putting together a weekly show on Jones, reports the Guardian. A third movie is also being planned which will see the return of Zellweger as the troubled fumbling British spinster.
                                                                                                                                                      
